description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Staff Nurse - Viking Ward - Up to 37.5 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you enjoy motivating patients to help them reach their full potential, and facilitating their safe discharge from hospital? We are looking for Registered Nurses to become part of our multidisciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Viking is a vibrant and friendly 28-bed ward at Crawley Hospital with close links to other community inpatient services. We pride ourselves in caring for patients of all ages with a variety of complex medical conditions and those who have post-surgical rehabilitation needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our multidisciplinary team includes a ward GP, Advanced Nurse Practitioners, Occupational Therapists, Physiotherapists and a social worker. To help our patients experience a high standard of care we also have input from Specialist Nurses, weekly consultant in-reach support and our community multidisciplinary teams, all helping to support discharges from hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Viking has a dynamic and compassionate team who aim to provide high quality, evidence-based care. The care and therapy our patients receive is delivered through careful patient-centred assessment with involvement from the patients and their families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our last Care Quality Commission inspection rated our community inpatient services as &lt;strong&gt;Outstanding&lt;/strong&gt; for Caring and our overall Trust rating as &lt;strong&gt;Good&lt;/strong&gt;. If you are passionate about making a difference and want to contribute to an organisation which is continuously striving to improve then we would love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return we can offer you:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working patterns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supportive learning environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dedicated career pathways and great opportunities for continuing professional development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commitment to and support for your health and wellbeing, including support to transition from a non-NHS environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS Pension Scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS discounts and salary sacrifice schemes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The surrounding area has good transport links to London and Brighton. We have onsite parking and are 15 minutes’ walk away from the train station and local town.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are committed to providing care in a compassionate and safe environment then working on Viking Ward in Crawley Hospital will be an opportunity for you to use your existing skills, gain new ones and be part of a great team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Theresa Fitton&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01273 696 011 ext. 6945, theresa.fitton@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
